6.1 Pivot Tables
Pivot tables allow you to summarize and analyze large datasets. Here's how you can create one:
  1.	Select your data range.
  2.	Go to Insert > Pivot Table.
  3.	In the Pivot Table field list: 
  o	Drag fields to the Rows, Columns, Values, and Filters sections.
  o	You can summarize data by summing, averaging, counting, etc.

6.2 Data Analysis Toolpak
The Analysis ToolPak is an Excel add-in that provides advanced statistical analysis tools:
  •	To enable it, go to File > Options > Add-ins, and check Analysis ToolPak.
  •	Common tools include regression analysis, histograms, and ANOVA.
